  <description><![CDATA[<p>Known as the ‘Pearl of Lake Maggiore’, this quaint lakeside town is situated in a sunny bay near the delta of the Maggia River and has a special charm. The lakeside promenade enjoys a wonderful panorama of <a data-udi="umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48" href="/{localLink:umb://document/476c8caf3fe84faab565f2d0f2e99f48}" title="Lake Maggiore">Lake Maggiore</a> and towards the Brissago islands and the old town with its cobbled streets and bell tower is home to a variety of little boutiques to explore. The regular bus and boat services bring visitors with ease to <a data-udi="umb://document/7b760653f95440289f984892a9c33c31" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7b760653f95440289f984892a9c33c31}" title="Locarno">Locarno</a> or other destinations on both the Swiss and Italian side of the lake, and there are plenty of walking opportunities from strolls along the lakefront, or walks higher up into the <a data-udi="umb://document/85fe05baebbf45fd9209de319bf06d35" href="/{localLink:umb://document/85fe05baebbf45fd9209de319bf06d35}" title="Ticino">Ticino</a> valleys.</p>
<p>In Ascona you'll have one of our reps's in resort who will know the local area and can assist you with any queries.</p>]]></description>
